==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Leatherwood
<hw>Leath"er*wood`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A small
branching shrub (<spn>Dirca palustris</spn>), with a white, soft wood,
and a tough, leathery bark, common in damp woods in the Northern United
States; -- called also <altname>moosewood</altname>, and
<altname>wicopy</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>leatherwork</ent>⟦br⟧
